20/04/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Development Minister Dimitris Sioufas visited Bucharest and Sofia on Thursday (April 19th) to discuss projects involving trade and the energy sector, as well as strengthening bilateral economic co-operation. 
In Bulgaria, Sioufas also met with officials to review latest developments in the Burgas-Aleksandropolis oil pipeline project involving Russia, Greece and Bulgaria. 
The Greek Parliament is expected to ratify the agreement next week.
Also Thursday, Greek Transport and Communications Minister Mihalis Liapis returned from Tokyo. 
Talks there focused on co-operation in communications and information technologies. 
(ANA-MPA - 19/04/07)
